text: Clark County is the name of twelve counties in the United States. Most, though not all, are named after two brothers: military hero George Rogers Clark in the Midwest, and explorer William Clark in the West. * Clark County, Arkansas * Clark County, Idaho * Clark County, Illinois * Clark County, Indiana * Clark County, Kansas * Clark County, Kentucky * Clark County, Missouri * Clark County, Nevada, the most populous county bearing the name Clark, containing Las Vegas * Clark County, Ohio * Clark County, South Dakota * Clark County, Washington * Clark County, Wisconsin == Other == * Clarke County * Lewis and Clark County, Montana
title: Clark County
